<section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-50 to-slate-100">
  <div class="container mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-hunter-green mb-4 font-serif">The Classical Lutheran Approach</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Our classical Lutheran approach to education follows the time-tested Trivium model, adapting to each child's natural development while integrating the Lutheran confession of faith.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <!-- Grammar Stage -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md border-b-4 border-academy-blue transform transition duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-lg">
        <div class="text-academy-blue mb-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-12 w-12" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 font-serif">Grammar Stage</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          In the Grammar Stage (K-5), students build a strong foundation of knowledge through memorization, recitation, and the joy of discovery, all within the context of the Lutheran confession.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Phonics-based reading instruction</li>
          <li>Singapore Math</li>
          <li>Latin foundations</li>
          <li>Rich literature and history</li>
          <li>Scripture and catechism memorization</li>
          <li>Hands-on science exploration</li>
          <li>Lutheran hymns and liturgy</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Logic Stage -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md border-b-4 border-hunter-green transform transition duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-lg">
        <div class="text-hunter-green mb-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-12 w-12" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M9 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m-3 7h3m-3 4h3m-6-4h.01M9 16h.01" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 font-serif">Logic Stage</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          In the Logic Stage (6-8), students begin to think more analytically and question the world around them. We teach them how to reason, analyze arguments, and think critically within the framework of Lutheran doctrine.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Formal logic instruction</li>
          <li>Socratic discussions</li>
          <li>Advanced Latin</li>
          <li>Pre-algebra and algebra</li>
          <li>Lutheran systematic theology</li>
          <li>Church history and confessions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Rhetoric Stage -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md border-b-4 border-academy-blue transform transition duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-lg">
        <div class="text-academy-blue mb-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-12 w-12" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 10h.01M12 10h.01M16 10h.01M9 16H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2v8a2 2 0 01-2 2h-5l-5 5v-5z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 font-serif">Rhetoric Stage</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          In the Rhetoric Stage (9-12), students learn to articulate and defend their ideas with wisdom, eloquence, and conviction, grounded in Lutheran theology and the liberal arts tradition.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Classical rhetoric and persuasion</li>
          <li>Advanced mathematics and sciences</li>
          <li>Great Books discussions</li>
          <li>Lutheran apologetics and worldview</li>
          <li>Senior thesis project</li>
          <li>Vocational discernment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>